The Intercom MCP server is an official, remotely hosted service that enables AI agents to securely access and interact with Intercom workspace data, such as conversations and contacts, via the Model Context Protocol [1][2][3]. It is currently supported only for US-hosted workspaces [1][2].

You can connect to the server using the streamable HTTP endpoint at `https://mcp.intercom.com/mcp` [1][4][2]. Authentication is handled via OAuth or a Bearer token [4][2]. Below is a standard configuration example for an MCP-compatible client:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "intercom": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "mcp-remote",
        "https://mcp.intercom.com/mcp"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

The server exposes tools for universal search and detailed data retrieval, allowing AI assistants to maintain workspace context without requiring local server deployment [1][4][2].
